</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="148" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,324,703,729]" box="[189,324,703,729]" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,703,729]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,703,729]" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[188,1401,751,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">
In both mtg trees the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1911" box="[604,752,751,777]" class="Insecta" family="Carsidaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carsidaridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1885" box="[805,948,751,777]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" genus="Pachypsylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[805,948,751,777]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">Pachypsylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is strongly or very strongly supported. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1911" box="[188,336,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Carsidaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carsidaridae</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1885" box="[359,502,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" genus="Pachypsylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[359,502,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">Pachypsylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1914" box="[521,702,788,815]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pachypsyllinae">Pachypsyllinae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heslop-Harrison" authorityYear="1958" box="[774,942,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Homotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Homotomidae</taxonomicName>
form a poorly supported sister group in the AN tree and both families are included in an unresolved basal assemblage in the 
<collectionCode box="[1223,1262,825,851]" country="Australia" name="CSIRO Canberra Rhizobium Collection" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">CC</collectionCode>
tree. In the molecular analyses by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cho G. &amp; Malenovsky I. &amp; Lee S." box="[457,658,861,888]" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" pagination="638 - 651" refId="ref21613" refString="Cho G., Malenovsky I. &amp; Lee S. 2019. Higher-level molecular phylogeny of jumping plant lice (Hemiptera: Sternorrhyncha: Psylloidea). Systematic Entomology 44 (3): 638 - 651. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12345" type="journal article" year="2019">
Cho 
<emphasis box="[512,563,861,887]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="1982" box="[670,799,861,887]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" genus="Celtisaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[670,799,861,887]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">Celtisaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1914" box="[814,995,861,888]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pachypsyllinae">Pachypsyllinae</taxonomicName>
) is recovered as weakly supported sister-group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heslop-Harrison" authorityYear="1958" box="[366,537,898,924]" class="Insecta" family="Homotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Homotomidae</taxonomicName>
, rather than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1911" box="[681,832,898,924]" class="Insecta" family="Carsidaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carsidaridae</taxonomicName>
, and the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1911" box="[1107,1258,898,924]" class="Insecta" family="Carsidaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carsidaridae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="1982" box="[1269,1398,898,924]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" genus="Celtisaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1269,1398,898,924]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">Celtisaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heslop-Harrison" authorityYear="1958" box="[242,410,935,961]" class="Insecta" family="Homotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Homotomidae</taxonomicName>
is well supported. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hollis D. &amp; Broomfield P. S." box="[645,983,935,961]" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" pagination="131 - 183" refId="ref22179" refString="Hollis D. &amp; Broomfield P. S. 1989. Ficus - feeding psyllids (Homoptera), with special reference to the Homotomidae. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology series 58: 131 - 183." type="book chapter" year="1989">Hollis &amp; Broomfield (1989)</bibRefCitation>
listed two putative morphological synapomorphies to link 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1911" box="[473,621,972,998]" class="Insecta" family="Carsidaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carsidaridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heslop-Harrison" authorityYear="1958" box="[680,853,972,998]" class="Insecta" family="Homotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Homotomidae</taxonomicName>
: 1) the presence of a pair of large tubercles on the metapostnotum, and 2) all three ventral sense organs of the metafemur in a basal position. These characters are present also in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1914" box="[539,720,1045,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pachypsyllinae">Pachypsyllinae</taxonomicName>
, though the tubercles on the metapostnotum are relatively small in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="1982" box="[290,419,1082,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" genus="Celtisaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[290,419,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">Celtisaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cho G. &amp; Malenovsky I. &amp; Lee S." box="[433,634,1082,1109]" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" pagination="638 - 651" refId="ref21613" refString="Cho G., Malenovsky I. &amp; Lee S. 2019. Higher-level molecular phylogeny of jumping plant lice (Hemiptera: Sternorrhyncha: Psylloidea). Systematic Entomology 44 (3): 638 - 651. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12345" type="journal article" year="2019">
Cho 
<emphasis box="[490,541,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
mention the bipartite male proctiger as a putative synapomorphy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heslop-Harrison" authorityYear="1958" box="[221,389,1119,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Homotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Homotomidae</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1914" box="[410,592,1119,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pachypsyllinae">Pachypsyllinae</taxonomicName>
. As in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Low" authorityYear="1879" box="[668,814,1119,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Aphalaridae</taxonomicName>
, the three taxa discussed here form, depending on the 
<typeStatus box="[231,282,1156,1182]" pageId="11" pageNumber="148">type</typeStatus>
of analysis, an unresolved basal (paraphyletic) assemblage or a monophylum with contradicting relationships between the constituent groups. For reasons of consistency, we include the three groups in the single family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1911" box="[442,594,1229,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Carsidaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carsidaridae</taxonomicName>
. The concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1911" box="[804,952,1229,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Carsidaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carsidaridae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Burckhardt D. &amp; Ouvrard D." box="[1004,1367,1229,1255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref21245" refString="Burckhardt D. &amp; Ouvrard D. 2012. A revised classification of the jumping plant-lice (Hemiptera: Psylloidea). Zootaxa 3509 (1): 1 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3509.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">Burckhardt &amp; Ouvrard (2012)</bibRefCitation>
is broadened here to include also 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heslop-Harrison" authorityYear="1958" box="[547,715,1266,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Homotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Homotomidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crawford" authorityYear="1914" box="[768,946,1266,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pachypsyllinae">Pachypsyllinae</taxonomicName>
which is transferred from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Low" authorityYear="1879" box="[1248,1395,1266,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Aphalaridae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
